                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 4.851,
                                "stop": 9.217,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The first is Tibble v. Edison International."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 9.217,
                                "stop": 17.051,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It is an ERISA case, a pension fund case, somewhat more technical and mollusk."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.051,
                                "stop": 27.445,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It concerns the application of the ERISA statute of limitations to a claim that a fiduciary has breached his duty of prudence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.445,
                                "stop": 35.885,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In 2007, the petitioners, who were employees of a company and beneficiaries of the plan, filed a lawsuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.885,
                                "stop": 60.127,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They said that the respondents, who were the trustees of the plan and others, violated their fiduciary duties with respect to six mutual funds by imprudently putting in the offers to the employees higher-priced retail class mutual fund shares when they were materially identical lower-priced institutional classed funds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.127,
                                "stop": 70.562,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As to the three funds that were added in 2002, now the suit was brought in 2007 so that\u0027s five years, the District Court agreed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.562,
                                "stop": 83.484,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They found that the respondents, the trustees and so forth, had not offered any credible explanation of why they offered retail classed funds that cost the plan participants wholly unnecessary fees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.484,
                                "stop": 97.346,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But in respect to the shares of the three funds that they got in the pension fund in 1999, the District Court said they are too late, they are too late."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.346,
                                "stop": 102.393,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They go back to 1999, that\u0027s more than six years before."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.393,
                                "stop": 112.943,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "There were no significant changes within the six-year statutory period that should have prompted a full diligence review and so we have to dismiss it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.943,
                                "stop": 116.011,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Ninth Circuit affirmed that dismissal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.011,
                                "stop": 124.841,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now in respect to the 1999 funds, the Ninth Circuit rejected the claims of the petitioner, they said they were untimely."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.841,
                                "stop": 155.488,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They were selected, the mutual shares, more than six years before and then it said, you can\u0027t establish a new breach within six years, a new breach of your duty of prudence by \u201cthe mere continued offer of a plan option without more\u201d and then it said the District Court was correct that maybe there was more, either could have been more, there could have been significant changes in that six-year period that would have required a full due diligence review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.488,
                                "stop": 160.589,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But the petitioners hadn\u0027t established that more, so it dismissed the case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.589,
                                "stop": 174.473,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And we are looking at that statute of limitations point and we decide that the Ninth Circuit applied an improper statutory bar that is it didn\u0027t interpret what the prudence rule is correctly."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.473,
                                "stop": 184.206,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We note that an ERISA fiduciary\u0027s duty is normally and as here the same as a fiduciary under the common law of trust."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 184.206,
                                "stop": 205.471,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now if you look to the common law of trust, you will see that a fiduciary must conduct a regular review of its investments and the nature and the timing of that review depend on the circumstances, the kind of fund it is, what the different circumstances are in that situation and so forth."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 205.471,
                                "stop": 220.86,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And as long as there is a duty to review and remove the imprudent investments and that review should have taken place within six years of suit then their claim was timely."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 220.86,
                                "stop": 232.537,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The parties all agree that the duty of prudence involves a continuing duty to monitor investments and to remove imprudent investments, at the trust law duty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 232.537,
                                "stop": 237.507,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The parties do disagree however about the scope of that responsibility."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 237.507,
                                "stop": 245.159,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Does it require a review of the funds that issue here, and if so, what kind of review does it require."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 245.159,
                                "stop": 259.528,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Under ERISA we know that the fiduciary has to discharge his responsibilities with the care, skill, prudence, and diligence that a prudent person acting in a like capacity familiar with such matters would use."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.528,
                                "stop": 263.338,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "So that\u0027s what we have to decide of using the right standard."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 263.338,
                                "stop": 267.463,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now we don\u0027t express any view of the scope of the fiduciary duty in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 267.463,
                                "stop": 278.64,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We set out the standard but we remanded for the Ninth Circuit to consider petitioner\u0027s claims that respondents breached a duty within the relevant six-year period."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 278.64,
                                "stop": 283.497,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We have to look at analogous trust law which they really didn\u0027t do."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 283.497,
                                "stop": 299.232,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Circuit may also consider the respondent\u0027s claim that the petitioner forfeited the right to make certain ones of these arguments but the upshot is we vacate the Ninth Circuit\u0027s determination, we remand the case and our decision in unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
